Preheat oven to 400 degrees F. Spray 8x8-inch glass baking dish with cooking spray; set aside. Combine cream cheese, garlic powder and pepper in large bowl. Add mozzarella cheese, drained tomatoes and artichokes to bowl; stir gently to combine. Place mixture in baking dish. Bake 15 to 20 minutes or until hot and bubbly. Serve with pita chips or French bread, if desired.